              "passage_text": "Currency management is not a peripheral concern for Brazilian investors — it sits at the core of portfolio construction. The strategic question is not whether to have dollar exposure, but how to size it, through which instruments, at what cost, and with what level of active management.\n\nThe most successful approaches combine:\n- A clear-eyed assessment of the investor's natural BRL or USD position\n- Awareness of the true cost of hedging through futures and the cupom cambial framework\n- Instrument selection aligned with tax efficiency and liquidity needs\n- A view — even a probabilistic one — on BRL fair value and its key drivers\n- Periodic rebalancing as exchange rates and portfolio values shift\n\nCurrency exposure, managed thoughtfully, transforms from a passive vulnerability into an active tool for portfolio resilience.",
