              "passage_text": "The following represents a selection of B3-listed companies recognized for consistent dividend/JCP distribution histories. This is not an exhaustive list and should not be interpreted as a buy recommendation:\n\n| Company | Ticker | Sector | Approx. Dividend Yield Range | Distribution Profile |\n|---------|--------|--------|------------------------------|----------------------|\n| Itaú Unibanco | ITUB4 | Banking | 5–9% | Quarterly JCP + annual dividend |\n| Banco do Brasil | BBAS3 | Banking | 7–12% | Semi-annual JCP + dividend |\n| Telefônica Brasil | VIVT3 | Telecom | 6–10% | Semi-annual distributions |\n| ISA CTEEP | TRPL4 | Electricity Transmission | 7–12% | Annual (large), intra-year JCP |\n| Engie Brasil | EGIE3 | Power Generation | 5–9% | Semi-annual |\n| CPFL Energia | CPFE3 | Utilities (integrated) | 5–8% | Annual |\n| TIM Brasil | TIMS3 | Telecom | 4–8% | Annual + JCP |\n| Petrobras PN | PETR4 | Oil & Gas | Variable: 5–25%+ | Quarterly (current policy) |\n| Taesa | TAEE11 | Electricity Transmission | 8–14% | Semi-annual |\n| Alupar | ALUP11 | Electricity Transmission | 6–10% | Semi-annual |\n\nYield ranges reflect historical variation across different market and interest rate conditions. Current yields should be verified against trailing twelve-month distributions and the current share price.\n\n---",
