              "passage_text": "Most Brazilian investors naturally begin with heavy BRL exposure: local equities, Tesouro Direto, LCI/LCA, CDBs, FIIs. The question is not whether to add dollar exposure, but how much and through which instruments.\n\nA simple framework for determining target FX allocation:\n\n| Investor Profile | Suggested USD/International Allocation | Primary Vehicles |\n|---|---|---|\n| Conservative, BRL income needs | 5-10% | IVVB11, gold ETF |\n| Balanced, medium-term horizon | 15-25% | BDRs, IVVB11, offshore fund |\n| Growth-oriented, long horizon | 25-40% | Direct offshore, BDRs, international ETFs |\n| Business owner with BRL revenues | 20-30% | Direct offshore, matching future USD expenses |\n\nThese are indicative ranges. The appropriate allocation depends heavily on the investor's specific liability structure, time horizon, tax situation, and view on BRL fair value.\n\n---",
